# tk4- extract

using the script export.sh extracted all `FB 80` sequential and PDS datasets as well and all `VB 255` PDS and all zip files. Zip files were then extracted. 

Created using hercules hyperion source.

Dasd sources from http://wotho.ethz.ch/tk4-/:

* tk4- current (at time of writting update 8): zip/tk4-_v1.00_current.zip
* tk4- sources: zip/tk4-source.zip
* tk4- cbt: zip/tk4-cbt.zip

## Folder Structure

Each each dasd that had files out from `dasdls` a folder was created. Within that folder every PDS has a subfolder made, if it was a sequential file it was placed in the DASD folder. 

```
**********************************************************************
*                                                                    *
* MVS 3.8j Tur(n)key 4- ("TK4-") is a ready to use OS/VS2 MVS 3.8j   *
* system built specifically to run under the Hercules System/370,    *
* ESA/390, and z/Architecture Emulator. It is an extension of the    *
* original MVS Tur(n)key Version 3 System ("TK3") created by Volker  *
* Bandke in 2002. See the User¿s Manual for credits and copyrights.  *
*                                                                    *
* Note: TK4- does not claim to be a new release of the original TK3  *
*       system, hence its name is TK4-, not TK4.                     *
```
